com.nimbusds.openid.connect.messages
Class AuthorizationRequest

java.lang.Object
  com.nimbusds.openid.connect.messages.AuthorizationRequest
All Implemented Interfaces:
Message, Request
public class AuthorizationRequest
extends java.lang.Object
implements Request

Authorisation request.

This class is not thread-safe.

Example HTTP request: 

 https://server.example.com/op/authorize?
 response_type=code%20id_token
 &client_id=s6BhdRkqt3
 &redirect_uri=https%3A%2F%2Fclient.example.com%2Fcb
 &scope=openid
 &nonce=n-0S6_WzA2Mj
 &state=af0ifjsldkj

Version:
0.9 (2012-05-12)
Author:
Vladimir Dzhuvinov

Creates a new minimal authorisation request. Use the setter methods for the optional request parameters.

Parameters:
rts - The response type set. Corresponds to the response_type parameter. Must not be null.
scope - The request scope. Corresponds to the scope parameter. Must not be null.
clientID - The client identifier. Corresponds to the client_id parameter. Must not be null.
redirectURI - The redirection URI. Corresponds to the redirect_uri parameter. Must not be null.
nonce - The nonce. Corresponds to the nonce parameter. Must not be null.

getResolvedRequestObject

public com.nimbusds.jwt.JWT getResolvedRequestObject()
                                              throws ResolveException
Gets the resolved OpenID request object.

The OpenID request object is resolved as follows:

  • If no request object is specified this method returns null.
  • If the request object is specified directly by a request parameter this method returns the same value as getRequestObject().
  • If the request object is specified by a request_uri parameter this method returns the referenced JWT.

Returns:
The resolved request object, null if not specified.
Throws:
ResolveException - For a request object URI that couldn't be resolved to a valid JWT.
